oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Loblolly pines planted in 1936 along the top of a twenty-foot high section of Fairview gully at the Natchez Trace State Forest have about stopped its expansion.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The kudzu below has helped stabilize the bottom of the gully but is killing the trees mingled with it and should be destroyed soon to prevent serious injury to the surrounding forest.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Forest reserves; Pines; Soil conservation; Vines
